cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL 

This paper explores patterns of music consumption and their relation to socioeconomic status using data from social media users of Last.fm and Twitter. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR), as well as Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) due to the use of natural language processing techniques in analyzing social media data.
